<plot>A pastiche of Norman Rydge, head of the Greater Union Organisation - a film agent whose monopolising tactics more or less spelt the end for the early Australian film industry. The title is a play on one of the most popular Australian silent films, 'The Shadow of Lightning Ridge' (1920), one of many movies featuring Australia's earliest cowboy star, Snowy Baker. 'Brownie' Vernon, the young American actress who co-starred, also returns in this movie.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?590085</url></doc>
